{% extends 'extractors/_meta/judge.j2' %}

{% block source_paths -%}
Source text:        {{ upstream['source-convert'].output.converted_path | default('(missing)', true) }}
Synthesis output:   {{ extracted.task_path | default('(missing)', true) }}
Replica root:       {{ vars.replica_root }}
Quintet:            {{ upstream['extract-classify'].output.quintet }}
Topic:              {{ upstream['extract-classify'].output.topic }}
{% if upstream['extract-summary'] is defined -%}
Summary:            {{ upstream['extract-summary'].output.summary | default('(no summary)', true) }}
{%- else -%}
Summary:            (no summary)
{%- endif %}

Wiki template:      {{ vars.wiki_template_path }}

{% set peers = [] %}
{% for tid, peer in upstream.items() if tid.startswith('extract-') and tid != task.id and peer.status == 'done' %}
{% set judge_id = 'judge-' + tid[8:] %}
{% set _ = peers.append({'task_id': tid, 'task_path': peer.task_path, 'verdict_path': upstream[judge_id].task_path if upstream[judge_id] is defined else None}) %}
{% endfor %}
Per-peer extractor outputs:
{% for peer in peers %}
- **{{ peer.task_id }}**: {{ peer.task_path }}
{%- endfor %}

Per-peer judge verdicts:
{% for peer in peers %}
- **{{ peer.task_id }}**: {{ peer.verdict_path | default('(no judge)', true) }}
{%- endfor %}

Per-kind destinations:
{% for kind, dest in vars.destinations.items() %}
- **{{ kind }}** → mode: `{{ dest.mode }}`{% if dest.get('folder') %}, folder: `{{ dest.folder }}`{% endif %}
{%- endfor %}
{%- endblock %}

{% block intro -%}
The synthesis agent wrote 0–2 vault-shaped markdown files into
the replica's ``21 WIKI/`` directory. Read each file (paths
listed in the synthesis output's ``paths`` array) and score it
against the rubric below. Most criteria score per page
(``target=<page title or path>``); page-count and orphan-coverage
criteria are ``target=null``.
{%- endblock %}

{% block criteria %}
1. **Page count.** Author should produce **0–2** synthesis
   pages. Score (target=null):
   - 0 pages — REVIEW only if the source is rich enough to
     warrant at least one synthesis page. Tag with
     ``category=missing_synthesis``.
   - 1–2 pages — PASS.
   - 3 or more — REJECT with ``category=over_fragmented``.
2. **Coverage of extracted items.** Read each peer
   extractor's output. For every kind that has items —
   regardless of whether ``destinations.<kind>.mode`` is
   ``synthesis`` or ``artifact`` — every item's name SHOULD
   appear at least once as a ``[[Name]]`` wikilink on some
   synthesis page — either as a ``- [[Name]] - …`` bullet
   under that page's ``## Key Concepts`` (or
   ``## Related artifacts``) section, OR as an inline
   ``[[Name]]`` wikilink in the page's opening rationale,
   ``## Overview`` prose, ``## Worked Examples`` body, or
   ``## Discussion`` text.

   Why both modes matter: synthesis-mode wikilinks resolve
   to nothing on disk (``strip-dead-links`` rewrites them to
   plain text post-gate). Artifact-mode wikilinks point at
   real replica pages — and the post-build ``prune-replica``
   task DELETES any artifact whose ``[[Name]]`` is not
   referenced by some synthesis page. Missing an artifact-
   mode wikilink therefore causes silent data loss (e.g.
   recipes vanish from the vault). Treat artifact-mode
   coverage with at least the same scrutiny as
   synthesis-mode coverage.

   Score (target=null), computed across the union of all
   extracted items from synthesis-mode AND artifact-mode
   kinds:
   - **All items covered, OR ≤25% uncovered AND ≤3 absolute
     orphans** → PASS.
   - More than 25% OR more than 3 orphans → REVIEW with
     ``category=orphan_synthesis_item`` and name the
     orphans, marking each as ``synthesis-mode`` or
     ``artifact-mode`` so the gate operator knows which
     orphans will be silently pruned vs. merely reformatted.
   - Fewer than 50% covered → REJECT with
     ``category=undercoverage``.
   - Any artifact-mode orphan whose extractor verdict was
     ACCEPT → REVIEW at minimum (data loss risk),
     regardless of percentage.

   Coverage is a quality concern for synthesis-mode items
   but a correctness concern for artifact-mode items.
3. **Frontmatter required.** Each synthesis page MUST have YAML
   frontmatter declaring at minimum ``type: synthesis``,
   ``title``, ``sources`` (non-empty list pointing at a
   ``10 SOURCES/`` page), and ``last_updated``. Missing →
   REJECT.
4. **Body structure.** Each page MUST have:
   - An opening rationale paragraph (≥80 chars) before the first
     ``##`` heading.
   - A ``## Overview`` section with multi-paragraph prose
     (≥200 chars combined).
   - An ASCII diagram inside a fenced code block, ≥4 lines,
     ≥80 chars total. Generic "title → bullets" → REJECT with
     ``category=generic_ascii``.
   - A ``## Key Concepts`` section composed exclusively of
     ``- [[Name]] - <summary>`` bullets, ≥3 entries. No
     ``###`` subsections inside Key Concepts (those drifted in
     from the old template; flag as
     ``category=stale_subsection``).
   Stub or missing sections → REJECT with
   ``category=thin_synthesis``.
5. **Inline wikilinks.** Every atomic name (from this page's
   key concepts or from any other extraction) mentioned in a
   prose field — opening rationale, Overview body, Key Concepts
   summary, Worked Examples body, Discussion — MUST have its
   first occurrence wrapped as a wikilink. Missing wikilinks →
   REJECT with ``category=missing_wikilinks`` and quote the
   unwrapped occurrence.
6. **Wikilink targets.** Every ``[[Name]]`` is fine to author
   even when no atomic page exists — the post-gate strip-dead-
   links task rewrites unresolved wikilinks to plain text. The
   judge does NOT score broken wikilinks; that is the strip
   task's responsibility. Score this dimension PASS by default.
7. **Discussion shape.** ``discussion`` is optional. When
   present:
   - **At most 3 topics.** 4 or more → REJECT with
     ``category=over_discussed``.
   - **Each topic** MUST carry a non-empty ``topic`` string and
     a ``summary`` of 1-2 sentences in the topic's own framing.
     Stub topics → REJECT with
     ``category=thin_discussion``.
   - **Actors** are optional; when supplied, every entry MUST
     have ``name`` and ``argument`` and the argument MUST be
     supported by the source. Fabricated positions → REJECT
     with ``category=invented_argument`` and quote the
     unsupported argument.
   When ``discussion`` is empty, score PASS without further
   checks — purely expository sources legitimately have no
   live debate to surface.
{% endblock %}
